%% Diagram: Inline vs async projection lifecycle
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant CmdH as Command handler
    participant ES as Event store
    participant Inline as Inline projection
    participant Bus as Subscription / CDC
    participant Async as Async projection
    participant Read as Read model
    Note over Client,Read: Inline (strong consistency)
    Client->>CmdH: send command
    CmdH->>ES: append events (txn open)
    ES->>Inline: apply event
    Inline->>Read: update read model (same txn)
    ES-->>CmdH: txn commit
    CmdH-->>Client: ack (read model already current)
    Note over Client,Read: Async (eventual consistency)
    Client->>CmdH: send command
    CmdH->>ES: append events (txn commit)
    CmdH-->>Client: ack
    ES-->>Bus: publish via subscription / CDC
    Bus->>Async: deliver (with possible duplicates / out-of-order)
    Async->>Read: idempotent upsert
    Async->>Bus: checkpoint(position)
